Post-Match Reflections: ‘It’s good for us – we needed this win,’ Babar told the post-match ceremony.
‘The wicket was not very helpful and was tricky early on. The Pakistan bowlers bowled well and we were never able to pick up the pace,’ said Canada captain Saad Bin Zafar.
Pakistan’s net run rate has improved to 0.191 and they are third behind India and USA, who have both won two games.
